  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I import my Gmail contacts into Skype?",
  "response": "To import your Gmail contacts into Skype, you typically need to follow these steps. Note that Skype may have undergone changes, so it's a good idea to check the latest instructions on Skype's help pages if needed. However, as of my last update, here is a general method to import your Gmail contacts:\n\n1. **Export Contacts from Gmail:**\n   - Sign in to your Gmail account.\n   - Click on the Google Apps icon (the grid) in the upper right corner and select **Contacts**.\n   - In the Contacts window, select the contacts you want to export (or select all).\n   - Click on the **More** option in the left-hand menu and select **Export**.\n   - Choose the format (usually vCard or CSV) that is compatible for importing into Skype. A CSV file is recommended for most applications.\n   - Click **Export** to download the file to your device.\n\n2. **Import Contacts to Skype:**\n   - Open the Skype application or go to the Skype website and sign in to your account.\n   - Click on your profile picture or icon in the upper left corner, then select **Settings**.\n   - Find the option for **Contacts** or **People** (this may vary based on the version of Skype you\u2019re using).\n   - Look for an option that says **Import contacts**, **Add contacts**, or similar.\n   - Select the option to upload the contacts file you exported from Gmail (this is usually a CSV file).\n   - Follow any additional prompts to finish the import process.\n\n3. **Sync Contacts:**\n   - In some versions of Skype, you can directly sync your contacts. Look for an option that says \u201cSync contacts\u201d or \u201cConnect to Google.\u201d\n   - If your Skype version supports it, authorize the access to your Google account, and it will pull in your contacts directly.\n\n### Note:\n- If you\u2019re using a newer version of Skype or a specific operating system, the steps might differ slightly. Therefore, it's advisable to check Skype's official support page for the most current instructions.\n- Ensure Skype supports importing from the format you've exported. If there are compatibility issues, you might need to adjust the file or check for alternative import methods.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during the process, please consult Skype's help documentation for troubleshooting tips.",
